                {
                    "name": "Forest Step",
                    "type": "stat_block_section",
                    "text": "<b>Frequency</b> three times per day; <b>Effect</b> The zomok teleports itself with the effects of a 5th-level <a aonid=\"69\" game-obj=\"Spells\"><i>dimension door</i></a> spell, but the zomok must begin and end the teleportation effect in forest terrain. The zomok regains 10d10 Hit Points during this teleportation. Creatures swallowed by the zomok are left behind. The zomok can't use Forest Step again for 1d6+1 rounds.",
